<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-10-06T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-10-06T21:00:00-05:00" n="147" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d147">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 FEAC/10–449: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Acting Political Adviser in Japan</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Sebald</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-10-06T21:00:00-05:00">October 6, 1949—9 p. m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>487. Reurtel 387, Oct 4.<note n="1" xml:id="d147fn1">Not
                                    printed.</note> In case USSR shld question right of Chi <gloss target="#t_Rep1">Rep</gloss> to sit for China in Allied Council
                                our <gloss target="#t_Rep1">Rep</gloss> might state that <gloss target="#t_Rep1">Rep</gloss> of Natl Govt of China is duly
                                accredited <gloss target="#t_Rep1">Rep</gloss> of China on Council;
                                that USSR is only Govt on Council which has withdrawn recognition
                                from Natl Govt; that other nations represented on Council all
                                continue to recognize Natl Govt as Govt of China; and that this Govt
                                perceives no reason to question right of duly accredited <gloss target="#t_Rep1">Rep</gloss> of China to sit.</p>
                            <p>Sovs did not raise question Oct 6 meeting <gloss target="#t_FEC1">FEC</gloss>. US <gloss target="#t_Rep1">Rep</gloss> prepared to
                                reply as above.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>